{% # Section v1.9.0 %}

{% comment %}
  Changelog
  - v1.9.0 — color scheme becomes an explicit local override. New `custom_color_scheme` checkbox (default false) gates the `color_scheme` picker (`visible_if`); the `color-scheme:<id>` modifier is emitted only when checked. Off = the section rides the global/substrate scheme (no modifier, cascades from `<body>`). Aligns with the substrate→local-override model; matches the gate now on group/columns/media. See `.context/docs/schema-conventions.md` § Color-scheme override + `theme-root.md` § Scheme paint.
  - v1.8.1 — bake seed-catalog metaobject handles into the four presets (content_width, block_rhythm, media_size, button_style). Metaobject settings store the entry handle, and Token seeds the same handles on every store, so these resolve anywhere — richer out-of-box presets without store-scoped GIDs. See `.context/docs/design-system-metaobjects.md` § Storing a metaobject reference value.
  - v1.8.0 — add four L2 presets (hero, features, content, cta) alongside the default empty Section. Each is a portable composition: color-scheme set via handle, all metaobject-picker settings (content_width, block_rhythm, media_size, button_style, …) left unset so they fall through to substrate defaults and carry no store-scoped GID. Block copy falls back to each block's own default content key. See `.context/docs/composition-strategy.md` § L2 — presets.
  - v1.7.0 — `--content-width` emission harmonized to rem (was px), matching the codebase-wide merchant-px / front-end-rem convention (gutter, text-style, spacing, block-layout-vars). Merchant input still px; converted at emit time via `divided_by: 16.0 | round: 3`. Per-project CSS doing arithmetic on `--content-width` (e.g., `calc(var(--content-width) - 2rem)`) now gets unit-consistent rem expressions.
  - v1.6.0 — block-rhythm now consumes the unified `--spacing-<handle>` namespace (paired with utility--css-variables v1.13.0 + layer-base.css spacing scale). Per-section dynamic style emits `--block-rhythm: var(--spacing-<picked-handle>)` instead of duplicating mobile/desktop px values; responsiveness propagates through the spacing token's @media branch. layer-theme.css inter-block margin rule reads `var(--block-rhythm)` (no mobile/desktop split at the section level). Merchant-facing setting unchanged.
  - v1.5.0 — rename custom element `<theme-section>` → `<token-section>` (theme fingerprint pass for porting agnostically). Per-project CSS using the tag selector `theme-section { ... }` must rename. Modifier value `theme-root` is unchanged (substrate selectors keep matching `[data-modifiers*='theme-root']`).
  - v1.4.0 — drop `layout` select setting per the subgrid migration. theme-section becomes an always-bleed-grid (no row/columns_N layout presets); merchants wanting row or multi-track compositions wrap in a `group` or `columns` block. Substrate CSS in `assets/layer-theme.css` no longer reads a `layout:<value>` modifier; emission of that modifier is removed.
  - v1.3.0 — add `layout` select setting (`column` / `row` / `columns_2/3/4`); emit `theme-root,layout:<value>,color-scheme:<scheme>` in `data-modifiers`. token-section becomes a parametrizable implicit container per the theme-root contract — substrate CSS in `assets/layer-theme.css` gates layout presets on the layout modifier. See `.context/docs/theme-root.md`.
  - v1.2.0 — replace `@theme` blocks wildcard with an explicit whitelist of the 9 shipped L1 blocks (+ `@app`) per the block-whitelisting convention in `composition-strategy.md`
  - v1.1.0 — add `block_rhythm` setting (spacing metaobject) + emit `--block-rhythm-{mobile,desktop}` variables for the inter-block margin rule in `core.css`
  - v1.0.0 — initial
{% endcomment %}

{% liquid
  assign content_width = section.settings.content_width
  assign block_rhythm = section.settings.block_rhythm
  assign base_selector = 'shopify-section-' | append: section.id

  assign scheme_modifier = ''
  if section.settings.custom_color_scheme
    assign scheme_modifier = ',color-scheme:' | append: section.settings.color_scheme
  endif
%}

<token-section data-modifiers="theme-root{{ scheme_modifier }}">
  {% content_for 'blocks' %}
</token-section>

{% capture dynamic_style %}
  {% if content_width and content_width != blank %}
    {%- assign content_width_rem = content_width.width.value | divided_by: 16.0 | round: 3 -%}
    --content-width: {{ content_width_rem }}rem;
  {% endif %}
  {% if block_rhythm and block_rhythm != blank %}
    --block-rhythm: var(--spacing-{{ block_rhythm.system.handle }});
  {% endif %}
{% endcapture %}
{% render 'utility--dynamic-style', base_selector: base_selector, css_content: dynamic_style %}

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "t:sections.section.name",
  "tag": "section",
  "class": "shopify-section--section",
  "blocks": [
    { "type": "spacer" },
    { "type": "separator" },
    { "type": "title" },
    { "type": "richtext" },
    { "type": "button" },
    { "type": "media" },
    { "type": "embed" },
    { "type": "group" },
    { "type": "columns" },
    { "type": "@app" }
  ],
  "disabled_on": {
    "groups": ["header", "footer"]
  },
  "settings": [
    {
      "type": "header",
      "content": "t:sections.section.settings.layout.content"
    },
    {
      "type": "metaobject",
      "metaobject_type": "content_width",
      "id": "content_width",
      "label": "t:sections.section.settings.content_width.label",
      "info": "t:sections.section.settings.content_width.info"
    },
    {
      "type": "metaobject",
      "metaobject_type": "spacing",
      "id": "block_rhythm",
      "label": "t:sections.section.settings.block_rhythm.label",
